6. Moral Hazard

Problem Description

Moral hazard occurs when actors are insulated from the consequences of their actions.

Financial systems frequently create moral hazard when institutions expect to be rescued from failure.

u-Kama Design Response

In the u-Kama architecture ecological outcomes cannot be overridden by financial incentives.

If ecological conditions degrade, qualification is lost and protocol recognition ceases.

Financial participants cannot shield ecological claims from failure.

This ensures that ecological reality remains the ultimate constraint on system outcomes.

