Closing Perspective

The architecture of u-Kama does not assume that participants will always behave perfectly.

Instead it assumes that systems must remain robust even when participants attempt to optimise their advantage.

By grounding verification in ecological processes, distributing observation across independent witnesses, and preserving evidence through cryptographic records, the system shifts incentives away from metric manipulation and toward ecological continuity.

In this way the protocol attempts to ensure that the measurement system remains aligned with the reality it is intended to represent.

Ecological truth is therefore not negotiated through metrics.

It is recognised when the land itself continues to function.

